EQUINE INFECTIOUS ANEMIA - SOUTH AMERICA (03): URUGUAY (FLORIDA) OIE
********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 13 May 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2019; 32(20) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=30443


Equine infectious anemia, Uruguay
---------------------------------
Information received on 13 May 2019 from Dr. Eduardo Barre Albera, Director General, Servicios Ganaderos, Ministerio de Ganader√≠a, Agricultura y Pesca, Montevideo, Uruguay

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 29 Apr 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 2 May 2019
Report date: 10 May 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 13 May 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 10 May 2007
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Equine infectious anemia virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Florida, Florida
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Apr 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 2200 / 18 / 0 / 18 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 0.82 / 0 / 0 / 0.82
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comment: Positive animals were sent to slaughterhouse. The premises were placed under restrictions. Epidemiological investigation is continuing, samples will be taken in series, at 45 days intervals, on all the animals of the farm for diagnostic purposes.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; selective killing and disposal; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Division of veterinary laboratories (DILAVE) (National laboratory) / Equidae / antibody detection ELISA / 24 Apr 2019 / Positive
Division of veterinary laboratories (DILAVE) (National laboratory) / Equidae / Coggin's test / 2 May 2019 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

